main event: On March 6, 1957, a ground-radar observation in Redmond, Washington reported seeing two dull grey and silvery kite-shaped objects rotating clockwise at an altitude of about 500 to 1000 feet for one minute.
interesting points: The sighting could indicate a non-natural object, but the evaluation for analysis was insufficient for a definitive conclusion.
The objects seemed to turn one revolution for each five degrees of arc, traveling from two to five o'clock in one minute.
A student pilot in the observing aircraft also sighted the object, initially mistaking it for a jet until it started to roll and rotate.
The report was classified and addressed to the Air Technical Intelligence Center at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base in Ohio.
The document features detailed descriptions of the observed UFO, including its orientation, color, and behavior.
sighted object: two dull grey and silvery kite-shaped objects
witnesses: Ground-radar, student pilot, and possibly others in the observing aircraft
